<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 1:14PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Carter County through
145 PM MDT...
At 113 PM MDT, trained weather spotters reported strong thunderstorms
along a line extending from 18 miles southwest of Ekalaka to near
Ridgeway to near Alzada. Movement was east at 70 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Alzada, Ridgeway, Belltower, Capitol, Albion and Mill Iron.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
